<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,635,1380]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,635,660]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Description.</emphasis>
Body (
<figureCitation box="[389,475,636,660]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 12" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1807,1830]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,337,1781]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,337,1783]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 12. Ochicanthon deplanatus (holotype). Dorsal habitus (10); base of pronotum and elytra (11); mesosternum and metasternum (12). Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/276625/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[446,475,636,660]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
) predominantly black with two orange-yellow spots along lateral margin of each elytron. Punctation on head and pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[646,726,671,695]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 12" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1807,1830]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,337,1781]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,337,1783]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 12. Ochicanthon deplanatus (holotype). Dorsal habitus (10); base of pronotum and elytra (11); mesosternum and metasternum (12). Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/276625/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[699,726,671,695]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
) consists of annular setiferous punctures separated by interval approximately equal to their diameter. Pronotum weakly convex, outline at base almost in line with that of elytral suture; laterobasal paramarginal ridge well marked, extended on slightly more than one third of pronotal length; setae almost indistinct, straight and recumbent. Elytra weakly convex; suture not raised; striae shallow, narrow, consisting of chains of oval depressions joined by straight sulci (
<figureCitation box="[903,987,815,839]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 12" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1807,1830]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,337,1781]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,337,1783]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 12. Ochicanthon deplanatus (holotype). Dorsal habitus (10); base of pronotum and elytra (11); mesosternum and metasternum (12). Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/276625/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[958,987,815,839]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
); interstriae fairly flat, finely punctate, uneven; background microsculpture coriaceous; lateral ridge posteriorly extended to level of apex of second stria. Mesosternum smooth, meso-metasternal line weakly arcuate, metasternum coarsely punctate (
<figureCitation box="[1220,1305,887,911]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 12" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1807,1830]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,337,1781]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,337,1783]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 12. Ochicanthon deplanatus (holotype). Dorsal habitus (10); base of pronotum and elytra (11); mesosternum and metasternum (12). Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/276625/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[1274,1305,887,911]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pygidium covered with shallow annular setiferous punctures becoming finer and sparser ventrally. Protrochanter with outer margin arcuate. 
<collectingCountry box="[332,388,960,984]" name="India" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Hind</collectingCountry>
wings present.
</paragraph>
